headline: U.S. Navy Partners with Palantir to Modernize Shipbuilding Supply Chain and Accelerate Shipbuilding
summary: DENVER, December 10, 2025--The United States Navy announced a groundbreaking partnership with Palantir Technologies Inc. (NASDAQ: PLTR) to deploy Palantir’s Foundry and Artificial Intelligence Platform (AIP) across the nation’s Maritime Industrial Base (MIB). The initiative, ShipOS, authorizes up to $448 million to accelerate the adoption of artificial intelligence and autonomy technologies across the industrial base.

headline: Wall Street is quiet as it waits for the Federal Reserve's announcement in the afternoon
summary: The U.S. stock market remains largely quiet on Wednesday as Wall Street waits to hear what the Federal Reserve will say in the afternoon about where interest rates may be heading.  Palantir Technologies added 1.7% after saying the U.S. Navy will use its artificial-intelligence technology as part of a $448 million program.  On the losing end of Wall Street was GameStop, which fell 6.1% after reporting weaker revenue for the latest quarter than analysts expected.
